    "## Image Import"

   "cell_type": "code",

    {
     "data": {

     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "# Import sourse image\n",
    "img = cv2.imread(\"localfiles/2colortexture.jpg\")\n",
    "st.show_img(img, True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Canny Edge Detection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# perform Canny edge tedection to find sharp gradients\n",
    "dst = cv2.Canny(img, 100, 300, None, 3)\n",
    "dstp = cv2.cvtColor(dst, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)\n",
    "\n",
    "st.show_img(dstp)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## HoughLines"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[[[297.75        0.5235988]]]\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Lets apply Standard HoughLine transform to detect lines\n",
    "dstp2 = cv2.cvtColor(dst, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)\n",
    "lines = cv2.HoughLines(dst, 1.5, np.pi / 120, 150, None, 0, 0)\n",
    "print(lines)\n",
    "# Below we will display the result by drawing lines\n",
    "if lines is not None:\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(lines)):\n",
    "        rho = lines[i][0][0]\n",
    "        theta = lines[i][0][1]\n",
    "        a = math.cos(theta)\n",
    "        b = math.sin(theta)\n",
    "        x0 = a * rho\n",
    "        y0 = b * rho\n",
    "        pt1 = (int(x0 + 1000 * (-b)), int(y0 + 1000 * (a)))\n",
    "        pt2 = (int(x0 - 1000 * (-b)), int(y0 - 1000 * (a)))\n",
    "        cv2.line(dstp2, pt1, pt2, (0, 0, 255), 3, cv2.LINE_AA)\n",
    "\n",
    "st.show_img(dstp2)\n"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "# We are looking for the intersection between the parametric line and the edges of the image, \n",
    "# to do this we need to evaluate the line at the edge values \n",
    "\n",
    "plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))\n",
    "for line in lines:\n",
    "    points = st.get_edge_points(line, img.shape[1], img.shape[0])\n",
    "    print(\"Edge point values: \\n\",points)\n",
    "    plt.plot(*zip(*points),color='orangered', linewidth=2)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  }
